Martin, Appellant, v. Women’s Mut. Ins. & Acc. Co., Respondent. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. January 10, 1890.)

Argued before Van Brunt, P. J., and Brady and Daniels, JJ.

James K. Averill, for appellant. John A. Kampiny, for respondent.

No opinion. Upon appellant’s stipulating to argue appeal at February Term, and paying $10, costs of motion, this motion will be denied.
